full_text: Screened by NARA, 9/25/2023 I June 16, 1972 To: U. S. Dept. of Justice Immigration & Naturalization Service Los Angeles, Calif. 90012 From: Mrs. Annie C. Yen 419 N. Plymouth Blvd. Los Angeles, Calif. 90004 Subj. Relationship between Petitioner and Beneficiary on Applying for Permanent Residence This is a certified letter to prove family relationship between petitioner and beneficiaries. The petitioner, Mrs. Annie C. Yen, U.S. Citizen through naturalization, #9504780, was born in Shanghai, China, on July 23, 1938, and is the eldest daughter of the following beneficiaries: Mr. Shu Tung Chiang Father CPA China, 6-23-10 Mrs. K. Y. Lo-Chiang Mother Housewife China, 8-23-15 They presently reside at E-8 Jen Ai Mansion, 37 Jen Ai Rd Sec. 4, Taipei, Taiwan, Republic of China. The petitioner is applying for permanent residence for her parents. The above information is furnished based on the attached census record from the Census Bureau, Taipei, Taiwan. JUN 16 1972 Seen at the Consulate of the Republic of China Los Angeles, Calif U.S.A. Consul of the Republic DEPARTMENT OF THE Los Angeles, California 610687 $200 LUS
